The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves the use of deep learning (cs.LG) and hand-crafted features (cs.MM) for feature representation. The research problem is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well.
